7 [ postsecondary education – TSgt Marshal Dakota
8 Roberts Gold Star Survivor Act – Gold Star – waiver
9 – spouse – children – noncodification -
10 codification – effective date ]
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
15 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
16 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "TSgt Marshal
17 Dakota Roberts Gold Star Survivor Act".
18 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3218.7-2 of Title 70, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 Within The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education, no
22 resident tuition or nonresident tuition shall be charged to the
23 spouse or children of a Gold Star recipient who was killed in the
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2961 Page 1

1 line of duty in any branch of the United States Armed Forces,
2 provided that either:
3 1. The Gold Star recipient was a legal resident of the State of
4 Oklahoma at the time of death; or
5 2. The spouse or child maintains residency in the State of
6 Oklahoma during enrollment.
7 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 3218.7-1, as
8 amended by Section 2, Chapter 382, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
9 Section 3218.7-1), is amended to read as follows:
10 Section 3218.7-1. A. Within The Oklahoma State System of
11 Higher Education, no fees nor room and board shall be charged to:
12 1. Children of Oklahoma peace officers as defined by Section
13 648 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes who have given their lives
14 in the line of duty;
15 2. Children of Oklahoma firefighters who have given their lives
16 in the line of duty;
17 3. Children of commissioned members of the Oklahoma Law
18 Enforcement Retirement System, who have given their lives in the
19 line of duty; and
20 4. Children of Oklahoma emergency medical technicians who have
21 given their lives in the line of duty; and
22 5. The spouse or children of a Gold Star recipient who was
23 killed in the line of duty in any branch of the United States Armed
24 Forces, provided that either:
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2961 Page 2

1 a. the Gold Star recipient was a legal resident of the
2 State of Oklahoma at the time of death, or
3 b. the spouse or child maintains residency in the State
4 of Oklahoma during enrollment.
5 B. Such waiver of fees and room and board shall be limited to a
6 period of five (5) years.
7 C. Such waiver of fees and room and board shall be a service
8 benefit of a commissioned member of the Oklahoma Law Enforcement
9 Retirement System.
10 D. For purposes of this section:
11 1. "Firefighter" means a volunteer firefighter or a permanent
12 salaried professional member of any fire department within the State
13 of Oklahoma; and
14 2. "Emergency medical technician" means a person volunteering
15 or employed as an emergency medical technician and who is licensed
16 as an emergency medical technician pursuant to Section 1-2505 of
17 Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
18 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 14-134, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 14-134. A. Within the system of career technology
21 districts, no resident tuition or nonresident tuition shall be
22 charged to the:
23
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2961 Page 3

1 1. Children of Oklahoma peace officers as defined by Section
2 648 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes who have given their lives
3 in the line of duty;
4 2. Children of Oklahoma firefighters who have given their lives
5 in the line of duty;
6 3. Children of members of the Oklahoma Law Enforcement
7 Retirement System who have given their lives in the line of duty or
8 whose disability is by means of personal and traumatic injury of a
9 catastrophic nature, as defined by Section 2-300 of Title 47 of the
10 Oklahoma Statutes, and occurred in the line of duty; and
11 4. Children of Oklahoma emergency medical technicians who have
12 given their lives in the line of duty; and
13 5. The spouse or children of a Gold Star recipient who was
14 killed in the line of duty in any branch of the United States Armed
15 Forces, provided that either:
16 a. the Gold Star recipient was a legal resident of the
17 State of Oklahoma at the time of death, or
18 b. the spouse or child maintains residency in the State
19 of Oklahoma during enrollment.
20 B. Such waiver of resident tuition and nonresident tuition
21 shall be limited to a period of five (5) years.
22 C. Such waiver of resident tuition or nonresident tuition to
23 the children of deceased peace officers and to the children of
24 deceased firefighters as provided for in this section shall be a
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2961 Page 4

1 serv ice benefit of each Oklahoma peace officer and Oklahoma
2 firefighter.
3 D. For purposes of this section:
4 1. "Firefighter" means a volunteer firefighter or a permanent
5 salaried professional member of any fire department within the State
6 of Oklahoma; and
7 2. "Emergency medical technician" means a person volunteering
8 or employed as an emergency medical technician and who is licensed
9 as an emergency medical technician pursuant to Section 1-2505 of
10 Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
